post_cb({"19025420": {"ParentId": "19025352", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_19025352_19025420_0\">I tried to use <code>break</code> but the control moved out of the parent for loop also.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>You must be confused. <code>break</code> only breaks out of the innermost loop/switch, so it <em>can't</em> have stopped the outer loop too (unless by chance the outer loop was on its last iteration, which gave you this false impression).</p>\n<p>When you are in doubt like this, you can either step through your code using a debugger, or at the very least insert \"tracing\" output in your code so that you can verify what it actually does:</p>\n<pre><code>for(int i=0;i&lt;5;i++)\n{\n    printf(\"outer loop %d\\n\", i);\n    for(int j=0;j&lt;5;j++)\n    {\n        printf(\"inner loop %d\\n\", j);\n        //checking some conditions here for true or false\n        if(false)\n        {\n            printf(\"breaking out of inner loop\\n\");\n            break;\n        }\n        else if(true)\n        {\n            printf(\"true in inner loop\\n\");\n        }\n    }\n    printf(\"finishing the outer loop %d\\n\", i);\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "2070725", "LastEditorUserId": "2070725", "LastEditDate": "2013-09-26T10:25:19.527", "Id": "19025420", "Score": "7", "CreationDate": "2013-09-26T10:13:40.747", "LastActivityDate": "2013-09-26T10:25:19.527"}, "19025461": {"ParentId": "19025352", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>If you use <code>break</code> in the inner loop then it will definitely move the control to the outer loop. </p>\n<p>I think what you might be missing is to reset your false condition after coming out of the inner loop.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "2078685", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "19025461", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-09-26T10:15:22.453", "LastActivityDate": "2013-09-26T10:15:22.453"}, "19025499": {"ParentId": "19025352", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>Break only breaks the loop in which it is used \nand btw if that condition is false it will never execute </p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "2672535", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "19025499", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-09-26T10:16:55.473", "LastActivityDate": "2013-09-26T10:16:55.473"}, "19025480": {"ParentId": "19025352", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>It's all based on logic on when you want to break out from the inner loops. Consider the following steps.</p>\n<pre><code>Do\n    For Int x = 1 To 10\n        Do\n            Break, Break, Break\n        Loop\n    Next x\nLoop\n</code></pre>\n<p>Try reconsidering your program logic and implement the break statements using flags.</p>\n<p>If you want, you could just overcome by breaking from the inner loops by using the goto statements.</p>\n<pre><code>int num[5][5][5];\n\nfor (int x = 0; x &lt; 5; x++)\n{\n    for (int y = 0; y &lt; 5; y++)\n    {\n        for (int z = 0; z &lt; 5; z++)\n        {\n            if (num[x][y][z] == 256)\n            {\n                cout &lt;&lt; \"Number has been found at location: \" &lt;&lt; x &lt;&lt; y &lt;&lt; z;\n                //break the three for loops here, it's unnecessary to check any other locations\n                goto finish;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\nfinish:\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "2818099", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "19025480", "Score": "-1", "CreationDate": "2013-09-26T10:16:15.690", "LastActivityDate": "2013-09-26T10:16:15.690"}, "19025516": {"ParentId": "19025352", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Yes your code is correct and it must work as you have expected.\nUnless you have compiled this one and execute something another. :-)</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1913812", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "19025516", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-09-26T10:17:59.273", "LastActivityDate": "2013-09-26T10:17:59.273"}, "19025352": {"CommentCount": "5", "ViewCount": "3747", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "2070725", "CreationDate": "2013-09-26T10:10:31.383", "LastActivityDate": "2013-09-26T12:33:32.357", "Title": "How to break out of inner for loop and get back to parent for loop", "LastEditDate": "2013-09-26T10:11:53.003", "Id": "19025352", "Score": "1", "Body": "<p>I have a code here,</p>\n<pre><code>for(int i=0;i&lt;5;i++)\n{\n    for(int j=0;j&lt;5;j++)\n    {\n        //checking some conditions here for true or false\n        if(false)\n        {\n            break out of this for loop;\n        }\n        else if(true)\n        {\n            printf(\"true\");\n        }\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>i want to break out of inner for loop and continue with the outer loop . I tried to use <code>break</code> but the control moved out of the parent for loop also.</p>\n<p>Any solution for this?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c>", "OwnerUserId": "2767930", "AnswerCount": "7"}, "19025518": {"ParentId": "19025352", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_19025352_19025518_0\">6.8.6.3 The break statement</p>\n<p id=\"so_19025352_19025518_1\">Constraints</p>\n<p id=\"so_19025352_19025518_2\">1 A break statement shall appear only in or as a switch body or loop body.</p>\n<p id=\"so_19025352_19025518_3\">Semantics</p>\n<p id=\"so_19025352_19025518_4\">2 A break statement terminates execution of the smallest enclosing switch or iteration\n  statement.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Quoted from ISO/IEC 9899:TC3</p>\n<p>So your break should work, as you don't use any pre alpha compiler.</p>\n<p>but the problem is more</p>\n<pre><code>if (false) //will never be executed, as false is ever fals\n{\n    //code gets never invoked\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>so you don't break out as you never invoke the <code>break;</code></p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "2003898", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "19025518", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2013-09-26T10:18:04.377", "LastActivityDate": "2013-09-26T10:18:04.377"}, "19025617": {"ParentId": "19025352", "CommentCount": "3", "Body": "<p>Try using a flag and checking it in your for loop conditional.</p>\n<pre><code>int stop = 0;\n\nfor (int i = 0; !stop &amp;&amp; i &lt; 5; ++i) {\n    for (int j = 0; j &lt; 5; ++j) {\n        if (false) {\n            stop = 1;\n            break;\n        }\n        // Condition when true does not need 'else' if breaking.\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1489354", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "19025617", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-09-26T10:23:34.310", "LastActivityDate": "2013-09-26T10:23:34.310"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_19025352_19025518_4": {"section_id": 3910, "quality": 0.5555555555555556, "length": 5}}, "n3337": {"so_19025352_19025518_4": {"section_id": 3770, "quality": 0.5555555555555556, "length": 5}}, "n4659": {"so_19025352_19025518_4": {"section_id": 4796, "quality": 0.5555555555555556, "length": 5}}}});